name: Brewer's Blackbird
overview: Rise and fall as they fly. Feed on the ground in the open, but often perch higher. Commonly seen with other species (cowbirds, starlings, Red-winged Blackbirds). They are active year round and are on the least concerned list for endangered species.
habitat: Generally found in open areas. Common throughout central and western North America. Often found near water. common in grasslands, meadows, golf courses, parks, etc.
